      "content": "You're right, it's not that simple, and it's not something you can just wish away. The pain and shame are a constant reminder of what's been lost, and it's natural to feel like it's all you are now. Sometimes, the only way to silence the noise is to give yourself permission to stop trying to be someone you're not. You don't have to pretend to be okay when you're not, and you don't have to put on a mask to hide the pain. It's okay to just exist in this darkness, even if it feels like it's all you can do.",
